###
Duck Hunt:  Compute Vision challenge for ECE 471

### Acknowledgement
Base of the code is from [this repo](https://github.com/borijang/gym-duckhunt.git).
Most of the sprites and game logic are borrowed from [this repo](https://github.com/mwrouse/DuckHunt-Python).

### Game Environment 
* Observation space: RGB image (1024x798x3)
* Action space: move in 8 directions + shoot, or
*               image coordinatess (x,y)

* Game session: 60 seconds

### Requirements
The environment is developed with:
* Python 3.7
* pygame 2.1.2
* numpy 1.21.5
* opencv-python 4.5.5
* ablumentations 1.1.0

### Installation 
Install the wheel:
`pip install --no-cache-dir ece71_duckhunt-*.whl`

Afterwards you can create the environment with `env = gym.make("DuckHunt-v0")`.

An example duck_hunt_main.py has been provided for you.



